---
// RecordFlow — Chapter 050 Lesson 2, "The verified-domain ceremony".
//
// A shape-only orientation map placed before the step-by-step ceremony, so the
// reader knows WHERE each piece lives before they start clicking around the
// Resend dashboard and their registrar. Three boxes, left → right:
//
//   Registrar DNS ─(authorizes & signs)─▶ Resend ─(delivers)─▶ Receiving inbox
//   (SPF/DKIM/DMARC)                    (send.<domain>)        (validates → PASS/FAIL)
//
// Deliberately theory-free. The WHY behind each record — the alignment rule, the
// SPF/DKIM/DMARC mechanics, the 2026 enforcement bar — is owned by Chapter 048
// Lesson 2; this figure only shows the three stations a signed message passes
// through. Each box stays a title + one muted under-label so the orientation
// reads at a glance and never competes with the prose.
//
// Built with <ArrowDiagram> (LeaderLine): the boxes are two-line custom HTML and
// match the sibling SendPath figure from Lesson 1, so the chapter's two flow
// diagrams share a visual language. Arrows are positioned from document.body, so
// the wrapping <Figure> MUST be expandable={false} — relocating the body into the
// lightbox breaks the leader lines.
//
// Sockets are right → left between adjacent boxes in one horizontal row; both
// labels sit lifted above the wire so they never collide with it. Chrome is
// theme-aware (Starlight gray/white vars flip light/dark). A margin:0 reset
// (.not-content) defeats Starlight's injected prose margins inside the figure.

import Figure from '../../../figures/Figure.astro';
import ArrowDiagram from '../../../figures/ArrowDiagram.astro';

// The three stations, left → right. `id` matches the arrow descriptors; `under`
// is the small muted label beneath each box title carrying the concrete detail.
const boxes = [
	{ id: 'rf-dns', title: 'Registrar DNS', under: 'SPF / DKIM / DMARC TXT records' },
	{ id: 'rf-resend', title: 'Resend', under: 'sends from send.<your-domain>' },
	{ id: 'rf-inbox', title: 'Receiving inbox', under: 'validates the signature → PASS / FAIL' },
];

const arrows = [
	// The records you publish are what let Resend send AS you — and what the inbox
	// later reads back to confirm the signature.
	{
		from: 'rf-dns',
		to: 'rf-resend',
		label: 'authorizes & signs',
		startSocket: 'right',
		endSocket: 'left',
		startSocketGravity: [60, 0],
		endSocketGravity: [-60, 0],
		labelOffset: [0, -28],
	},
	// The vendor's wire to the receiving inbox.
	{
		from: 'rf-resend',
		to: 'rf-inbox',
		label: 'delivers',
		startSocket: 'right',
		endSocket: 'left',
		startSocketGravity: [60, 0],
		endSocketGravity: [-60, 0],
		labelOffset: [0, -28],
	},
];
---

<Figure expandable={false}>
	<ArrowDiagram arrows={arrows}>
		<div class="rf not-content">
			{
				boxes.map((box) => (
					<div class="rf-box" id={box.id}>
						<span class="rf-title">{box.title}</span>
						<span class="rf-under">{box.under}</span>
					</div>
				))
			}
		</div>
	</ArrowDiagram>
	<Fragment slot="caption">
		The three records you publish at your registrar are what let the receiving
		inbox confirm a message really came from you. Shape only — the alignment
		mechanics are owned by <a
			href="/048-sender-identity-and-deliverability/2-authenticating-the-sender---spf-dkim-dmarc/"
			>chapter 48</a
		>.
	</Fragment>
</Figure>

<style>
	.rf {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: nowrap;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: space-between;
		gap: 96px;
		margin: 0;
		padding: 24px 4px 14px;
		font-family:
			ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
	}

	.rf-box {
		position: relative;
		box-sizing: border-box;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 4px;
		flex: 0 1 auto;
		padding: 12px 16px;
		border-radius: 10px;
		border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5, #cbd5e1);
		background: var(--sl-color-bg, transparent);
		text-align: center;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.rf-title {
		font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, monospace;
		font-size: 0.86rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		line-height: 1.2;
		white-space: nowrap;
		color: var(--sl-color-white, #1e293b);
		margin: 0;
	}

	.rf-under {
		font-size: 0.66rem;
		line-height: 1.25;
		white-space: nowrap;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-3, #64748b);
		margin: 0;
	}

	/* Narrow viewports: stack the three boxes; the right → left sockets degrade to
	   vertical arcs between stacked boxes — readable, and the labels still float in
	   the gaps. */
	@media (max-width: 720px) {
		.rf {
			flex-direction: column;
			gap: 52px;
		}
		.rf-box {
			width: min(20rem, 100%);
		}
		.rf-under {
			white-space: normal;
		}
	}
</style>
